# Backend Standards

## FastAPI Patterns
- All routes use `async def` — no synchronous route handlers
- Use Pydantic v2 models for all request/response bodies
- Group routes with `APIRouter` in `/routers/` — never define routes in `main.py`
- Use `Depends()` for shared logic (e.g., get_current_persona, get_db)

```python
# ✅ GOOD
from fastapi import APIRouter, Depends
from app.models import EcoScoreResponse
from app.dependencies import get_hotel_service

router = APIRouter(prefix="/hotels", tags=["hotels"])

@router.get("/{hotel_id}/eco-score", response_model=EcoScoreResponse)
async def get_eco_score(
    hotel_id: str,
    hotel_service: HotelService = Depends(get_hotel_service),
) -> EcoScoreResponse:
    ...
```

## Type Annotations
- Every function must have full type annotations on all parameters and return types
- Use `list[T]`, `dict[K, V]` (Python 3.10+ style) — not `List[T]`, `Dict[K, V]`
- Use `X | None` instead of `Optional[X]`

## Pydantic Models
- All models in `/app/models/` — one file per domain (hotel.py, guest.py, brief.py)
- Use `model_config = ConfigDict(from_attributes=True)` for ORM-compatible models

## Data Layer
- All seed data loaded once at startup from `/data/seeds/*.json`
- Loaded via `app/data/loader.py` into in-memory dicts keyed by ID
- No actual DB queries for the demo — everything is from the in-memory seed store
- Production path (what we'd replace with): documented in comments and PRD

## LLM Calls
- All LLM calls in `/app/services/llm_service.py`
- Always have a `USE_MOCK_LLM=true` env fallback that returns a hardcoded fixture
- Log every LLM call with input token count estimate

## CORS
- Allow `http://localhost:3000` (Next.js dev) in development
- Set via `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` env var

## File Structure
```
backend/
├── app/
│   ├── main.py            # FastAPI app + CORS + startup
│   ├── routers/           # hotels.py, guests.py, brief.py, partners.py
│   ├── models/            # Pydantic schemas
│   ├── services/          # business logic (eco_service.py, brief_service.py, llm_service.py)
│   ├── data/              # loader.py — loads seed JSON into memory
│   └── dependencies.py    # FastAPI Depends() helpers
├── data/
│   └── seeds/             # hotels.json, partners_*.json, guests.json, stays.json
├── tests/
└── requirements.txt
```
